{
  "id": "c0c0c0c0-0016-0000-0000-000000000000",
  "name": "Common Code Gotchas",
  "type": "871ae771-b9b1-4f40-8c7f-d9038bfb69c3",
  "created": 1738454400000,
  "modified": 1774988060652,
  "content": {
    "description": [
      ":doc",
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Documented pitfalls discovered during Hobson development. Each was a real bug that cost debugging time."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "The parseInt Zero Trap"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        [
          ":strong",
          {
            "s": "Problem:"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "parseInt(\"0px\") || fallback"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " treats 0 as falsy."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": "// WRONG — window at x=0 jumps to fallback position\nconst x = parseInt(wrapper.style.left) || 50;\n\n// CORRECT — 0 is a valid position\nconst leftPx = parseInt(wrapper.style.left);\nconst x = isNaN(leftPx) ? 50 : leftPx;"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        [
          ":strong",
          {
            "s": "Why this matters:"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " Window position (0, 0) is valid. The "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "||"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " operator treats "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "0"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " as falsy, triggering the fallback. The "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "isNaN()"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " check correctly detects only parse failures."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        [
          ":strong",
          {
            "s": "Pattern to use everywhere:"
          }
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": "const parsed = parseInt(string);\nconst value = isNaN(parsed) ? defaultValue : parsed;"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Backward Compatibility: String → Object Attachments"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Attachments evolved from string arrays to positioned objects:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": "// Old format\nattachments: [\"item-1\", \"item-2\"]\n\n// Current format\nattachments: [{ id: \"item-1\", view: { type: \"...\", x: 20, y: 20, ... } }]"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "All code that reads attachments must handle both:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": "const childId = typeof child === 'string' ? child : child.id;"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "String-format attachments convert to object format on first interaction."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Reading Position from DOM, Not Closures"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "When starting a drag, read the current position from the DOM element — not from the render-time closure:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": "// WRONG — uses stale render-time data\nconst startLeft = child.x;\n\n// CORRECT — reads actual current DOM position\nconst leftPx = parseInt(wrapper.style.left);\nconst startLeft = isNaN(leftPx) ? child.x : leftPx;"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "See "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "c0c0c0c0-0011-0000-0000-000000000000"
          },
          {
            "s": "Stale Closure Prevention"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " for the full pattern."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Updating Multiple Properties Together"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "When modifying item data, include all properties — not just the one you're changing:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": "// WRONG — loses other properties when converting string to object\nconst updates = { x: newX, y: newY };\n\n// CORRECT — includes all properties for complete data\nconst updates = {\n  x: newX, y: newY,\n  width: width, height: height,\n  z: currentZ\n};"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "This is especially important when converting string-format attachments to object format."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Global Listeners for Drag"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Attach "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "mousemove"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " and "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "mouseup"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " listeners to "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "document"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ", not to the element being dragged:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": "// WRONG — loses drag if mouse leaves the element\ntitlebar.onmousemove = handleDrag;\n\n// CORRECT — captures drag everywhere\ndocument.addEventListener('mousemove', handleDrag);\ndocument.addEventListener('mouseup', handleDragEnd);"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "The mouse can leave the window during a drag. Titlebar-only listeners lose the interaction."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "setTimeout(0) for Post-Render Work"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "After replacing DOM content, use "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "setTimeout(..., 0)"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " to defer operations that depend on the new DOM being in place:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": "mainView.appendChild(newContent);\nsetTimeout(() => {\n  // Now the DOM is fully rendered and measurable\n  restoreScrollPositions();\n}, 0);"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Hob Atoms and Re-render Loops"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        [
          ":strong",
          {
            "s": "Problem:"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " A Hob view creates atoms during its tracked evaluation. When a click handler calls "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "(reset! my-atom new-val)"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ", the atom mutation callback triggers a full re-render of the same view, creating fresh atoms with default values — wiping all state."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        [
          ":strong",
          {
            "s": "Why it happens:"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " During "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "renderHobView"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ", "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "startTracking()"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " is active. "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "(deref my-atom)"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " inside build functions calls "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "recordAtomAccess(atom)"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ", registering the atom as a dependency. Later, "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "(reset! my-atom ...)"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " fires "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "_atomMutationCallback"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " → rendering system finds dependents → schedules re-render → entire Hob code re-evaluated with fresh atoms."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        [
          ":strong",
          {
            "s": "The fix (platform-level):"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " Atoms are tagged with "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "_ownerCtx"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " (the tracking context ID active when they were created). "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "recordAtomAccess"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " skips self-owned atoms — atoms created by a view's own evaluation don't become dependencies of that view. This means "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "reset!"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " on view-local atoms drives local updates via "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "dom-set-content!"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " without triggering re-renders."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        [
          ":strong",
          {
            "s": "Symptoms if broken:"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " Click handlers produce a brief DOM flash then revert. State appears to reset after every interaction. Console may show "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "[Reactivity] Cycle detected"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": "."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "See Also"
        }
      ],
